Message: Variable value not found in non-extensible codelist
Description: Variable must be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist. New terms cannot be added into non-extensible codelists.

Message: Variable value not found in extensible codelist
Description: Variable should be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist. New terms can be added as long as they are not duplicates, synonyms or subsets of existing standard terms.

Message: Coded and Decoded values do not have the same Code in CDISC CT
Description: Paired variables such as TEST/TESTCD must be populated using terms with the same Codelist Code value in CDISC control terminology. There is one-to-one relationship between paired variable values defined in CDISC control terminology by Codelist Code value.

Message: Variable value not found in non-extensible codelist when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable must be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist when its value level condition is met. New terms cannot be added into non-extensible codelists.

Message: Variable value not found in extensible codelist when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable should be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist when its value level condition is met. New terms can be added as long as they are not duplicates, synonyms or subsets of existing standard terms.

Message: Coded and Decoded values do not have the same Code in CDISC CT when value-level condition occurs
Description: Paired variables such as TEST/TESTCD must be populated using terms with the same Codelist Code value in CDISC control terminology. There is one-to-one relationship between paired variable values defined in CDISC control terminology by Codelist Code value within the same value level condition.

Message: Missing define.xml file
Description: Guidance provided by regulatory agencies states that eCTD submissions must include a define.xml file for each study in Module 4 (nonclinical) and Module 5 (clinical). Note: Refer to the data standards catalog by the relevant Regulatory Agency for acceptance of standards and their versions.

Message: No records in data source
Description: Domain table should have at least one record.

Message: Null value in variable marked as Required
Description: Required variables (where Core attribute is 'Req') cannot be null for any records.

Message: Invalid ISO 8601 value for variable
Description: Value of Dates/Time variables (*DTC) must conform to the ISO 8601 international standard.

Message: Inconsistent value for DOMAIN
Description: Domain Abbreviation (DOMAIN) variable should be consistent with the name of the dataset.

Message: Duplicate value for --SEQ variable
Description: The value of Sequence Number (--SEQ) variable must be unique for each record within a domain and within each Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) or Pool Identifier (POOLID) variables value when they are present in the domain. Exclusions are DE, DO, DT, DU, and DX domains.

Message: Inconsistent value for Standard Units
Description: Standard Units (--STRESU) must be consistent for all records with the same Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD), Object of the Observation (--OBJ), Measurement Test, or Examination Detail (--TSTDTL), Category (--CAT), Specimen Type (--SPEC), Method of Test or Examination (--METHOD), and Marker String (--MRKSTR).

Message: --STDY is after --ENDY
Description: Study Day of Start of Event, Exposure or Observation (--STDY) must be less or equal to Study Day of End of Event, Exposure or Observation (--ENDY).

Message: --STDTC is after --ENDTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Event, Exposure or Observation (--STDTC) must be less or equal to End Date/Time of Event, Exposure or Observation (--ENDTC).

Message: Negative value for --DOSE
Description: Non-missing Dose (--DOSE) value must be greater than or equal to 0.

Message: Negative value for --DUR
Description: Non-missing Duration of Event, Exposure or Observation (--DUR) value must be greater than or equal to 0.

Message: Missing value for --STRESC when --DRVFL='Y'
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Format (--STRESC) value should not be null when Derived Flag (--DRVFL) value is 'Y'.

Message: Invalid value for --TEST variable
Description: The value of Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST) should be no more than 40 characters in length.

Message: Invalid value for --TESTCD variable
Description: The value of a Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD) variable should be limited to 8 characters, cannot start with a number, and cannot contain characters other than letters in upper case, numbers, or underscores.

Message: Invalid value for --PARM variable
Description: The value of Parameter (--PARM) variable should be no more than 40 characters in length.

Message: Invalid value for --PARMCD variable
Description: The value of Parameter Short Name (--PARMCD) variables should be no more than 8 characters in length.

Message: Missing value for --STAT when --REASND is provided
Description: Completion Status (--STAT) should be set to 'NOT DONE' when Reason Not Done (--REASND) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --DTC when --ENDTC is provided
Description: Date/Time of Collection (--DTC) should not be null when End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC) is not null.

Message: --DTC is after --ENDTC
Description: Date/Time of Specimen Collection (--DTC) must be less or equal to End Date/Time of Specimen Collection (--ENDTC).

Message: Missing value for --ORRESU when --ORRES is provided
Description: Original Units (--ORRESU) should not be null when Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) is provided is a numeric result.

Message: Missing value for --ORRES when --ORRESU is provided
Description: Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) should not be null when Original Units (--ORRESU) is provided.

Message: Value for --STNRHI is less than value for --STNRLO
Description: Reference Range Upper Limit-Std Units (--STNRHI) value must be greater than or equal to Reference Range Lower Limit-Std Units (--STNRLO) value.

Message: Missing value for --STRESU when --STRESC is provided
Description: Standard Units (--STRESU) should not be null when Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) is provided as a numeric result.

Message: Missing value for --STRESC when --STRESU is provided
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) should not be null when Standard Units (--STRESU) is provided.

Message: Missing values for --STDTC, --STRF and --STRTPT when --ENDTC, --ENRF or --ENRTPT is provided
Description: Start Date/Time of Observation (--STDTC), Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF) or Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) should not be null when End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC), End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF) or End Relative to Reference Time Period (--ENRTPT) is not null.

Message: Missing value for --TPT when --TPTNUM is provided
Description: Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) should not be null when Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --TPTNUM when --TPT is provided
Description: Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) should not be null when Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --TPTREF when --ELTM is provided
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) should not be null when Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref (--ELTM) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --DOSU when --DOSE, --DOSTXT or --DOSTOT is provided
Description: Dose Units (--DOSU) must be populated when Dose per Administration (--DOSE), Dose Description (--DOSTXT) or Total Daily Dose (--DOSTOT) is provided.

Message: Missing value for --STRESC when --ORRES is provided
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) must be populated when Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) is provided.

Message: Value for variable not found in user-defined codelist
Description: Variable values should be populated with terms found in the user-defined codelist associated with the variable in define.xml.

Message: Value of Study Day variable equals 0
Description: Study Day variables (*DY) value should not equal 0.

Message: Inconsistent value for --TEST within --TESTCD
Description: All values of Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST) should be the same for a given value of Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD).

Message: Missing value for --TRTV when --VAMT is not null
Description: Treatment Vehicle (--TRTV) should be provided when Treatment Vehicle Amount (--VAMT) is specified.

Message: Missing value for --VAMTU when --VAMT is populated
Description: Treatment Vehicle Amount Units (--VAMTU) should not be null when Treatment Vehicle Amount (--VAMT) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --STRESC when --RESCAT is populated
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) should be provided when Result Category (--RESCAT) is specified.

Message: Inconsistent value for QLABEL within QNAM
Description: All values of Qualifier Variable Label (QLABEL) should be the same for a given value of Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM).

Message: Missing value for --ORRES when --STAT or --DRVFL is not populated
Description: Status (--STAT) should be set to 'NOT DONE' or Derived Flag (--DRVFL) should have a value of 'Y' when Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) is null.

Message: Missing value for --STTPT when --STRTPT is populated
Description: Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) must not be null when Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) is provided.

Message: Missing value for --ENTPT when --ENRTPT is populated
Description: End Reference Time Point (--ENTPT) must not be null when End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) is provided.

Message: Variable in define.xml is not present in the dataset
Description: Variables listed in the data definition document (define.xml) should be included in the dataset.

Message: Variable appears in dataset, but is not in SDTM model
Description: Only variables listed in SDTM model should appear in a dataset. New sponsor defined variables must not be added, and existing variables must not be renamed or modified.

Message: Define.xml/dataset variable type mismatch
Description: Variable DataType in define.xml must match variable Type in dataset. Define-XML data types of 'integer' and 'float' match dataset type of 'Num', all other match 'Char'.

Message: Variable in dataset is not present in define.xml
Description: Variables included in the dataset must be described in the data definition document (define.xml).

Message: Domain referenced in define.xml, but dataset is missing
Description: Domains referenced in data definition document (define.xml) should be included in the submission.

Message: Incompatible data source
Description: Domain table must have a valid format (e.g., SAS transport (XPORT) v.5 or text-delimited).

Message: Subject is not present in DM domain
Description: All Subjects (USUBJID) must be present in Demographics (DM) domain.

Message: Invalid ARMCD
Description: Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL') or were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN').

Message: Invalid ETCD
Description: Element Code (ETCD) values should match entries in the Trial Elements (TE) dataset, except for unplanned Element (ETCD = 'UNPLAN').

Message: Invalid ARM/ARMCD
Description: The combination of Description of Planned Arm (ARM) and Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) values must match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL') or were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN').

Message: Invalid RDOMAIN
Description: Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN) must have a valid value of Domains included in the study data.

Message: Invalid IDVAR
Description: Identifying Variable (IDVAR) must have a valid value of variables from a referenced Domain.

Message: Invalid referenced record
Description: Reference record defined by Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN), Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID), Identifying Variable (IDVAR) and Identifying Variable Value (IDVARVAL) must exist in the target Domain.

Message: Exposure end date is after the latest Disposition date
Description: End Date/Time of Treatment (EXENDTC) should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC). Investigator should provide a date of study discontinuation for each subject in Disposition (DS) domain. If the study is ongoing, Parameter Value (TSVAL) for the 'ONGOSIND/Ongoing Study Indicator' parameter should be set to 'Y' in the Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Duplicate USUBJID in DM within STUDYID
Description: The value of Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variable must be unique for each subject across all trials in the submission. In the Demographics (DM) domain, there should only be one record per subject.

Message: Negative or zero value for AGE
Description: The value of Age (AGE) cannot be less than or equal to 0.

Message: SUPPQUAL duplicate records
Description: All SUPPQUAL Domains records are associated with a single parent record and must have a unique combination of Study Identifier (STUDYID), Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID), Identifying Variable (IDVAR), Identifying Variable Value (IDVARVAL) and Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM) variable value. For all SUPPQUAL domain record all The QNAM variable should be unique for each parent record.

Message: RFSTDTC is not provided for a randomized subject
Description: Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) should be populated for all randomized subjects, those where Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) is not equal to 'SCRNFAIL' or 'NOTASSGN' or null.

Message: RFENDTC is not provided for a randomized subject
Description: Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC) should be populated for all randomized subjects, those where Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) is not equal to 'SCRNFAIL' or 'NOTASSGN' or null. If the study is ongoing, Parameter Value (TSVAL) for the 'ONGOSIND/Ongoing Study Indicator' parameter should be set to 'Y' in the Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing values for TEENRL and TEDUR
Description: At least one of Rule for End of Element (TEENRL) or Planned Duration of Element (TEDUR) should be populated.

Message: Missing value for SEUPDES when ETCD='UNPLAN'
Description: Description of Unplanned Element (SEUPDES) should be populated when subject's experience for a particular period of time is represented as an unplanned Element, where Element Code (ETCD) is equal to 'UNPLAN'.

Message: Invalid usage of SUPPQUAL for non-general-observation-class Domain
Description: Supplemental Qualifiers special purpose dataset (SUPP--) can only be used to capture non-standard variables and their association to parent records in general-observation-class datasets (Events, Findings, Interventions) and Demographics. Another exception is Subject Visits domain in SDTM-IG prior v3.4.

Message: SUBJID is not unique for each subject within study
Description: The value of Subject Identifier for the Study (SUBJID) variable must be unique for each subject within the study.

Message: RFSTDTC is after RFENDTC
Description: Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) must be less than or equal to Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC).

Message: Invalid value for ARMCD exceeding 20 characters
Description: The value of Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) should be no more than 20 characters in length.

Message: Invalid STUDYID
Description: Study Identifier (STUDYID) values must match the STUDYID in Demographics (DM) domain.

Message: Invalid value for ETCD
Description: The value of Element Code (ETCD) should be no more than 8 characters in length.

Message: ELEMENT value is populated when ETCD= 'UNPLAN'
Description: Description of Element (ELEMENT) should be null when subject's experience for a particular period of time is represented as an unplanned Element, where Element Code (ETCD) is equal to 'UNPLAN'.

Message: Invalid ISO 8601 value for variable
Description: Value of Duration, Elapsed Time, and Interval variables (--DUR, --ELTM, --EVLINT, --STINT, --ENINT, TDSTOFF, TDTGTPAI, TDMINPAI, TDMAXPAI) must conform to the ISO 8601 international standard.

Message: Invalid ETCD/ELEMENT
Description: The combination of Element Code (ETCD) and Description of Element (ELEMENT) values should match entries in the Trial Elements (TE) dataset, except for unplanned Element (ETCD = 'UNPLAN').

Message: Invalid TAETORD
Description: Order of Element within Arm (TAETORD) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset.

Message: Missing DM dataset
Description: Demographics (DM) dataset must be included in every submission.

Message: Unexpected character value in variable
Description: Character values should not have leading space ' ' characters, carriage returns, or '.' as an entire value. The only exceptions are COVALn and TSVALn variables.

Message: Invalid value for QNAM variable
Description: The value of Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM) should be limited to 8 characters, cannot start with a number, and cannot contain characters other than letters in upper case, numbers, or underscores.

Message: Invalid value for RELTYPE variable
Description: Relationship Type (RELTYPE) must be null when Identifying Variable (IDVAR) is populated with a --SEQ value.

Message: Non-unique value for ELEMENT within ETCD
Description: Description of Element (ELEMENT) must have a unique value for a given value of Element Code (ETCD) within the domain.

Message: Non-ASCII or non-printable characters in variable
Description: Variables value must not include non-ASCII or non-printable characters (outside of 32-126 ASCII code range), limited to variables which values may be converted into new variable name or label (--TEST, --TESTCD, --PARM, --PARMCD, QLABEL, QNAM).

Message: Value for --STRF is populated when RFSTDTC is null
Description: Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF) should not be populated for subjects with missing value for Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC).

Message: Value for --ENRF is populated when RFENDTC is null
Description: End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF) should not be populated for subjects with missing value for Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC).

Message: Inconsistent value for ARM
Description: A value for Description of Planned Arm (ARM) must have a unique value for Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) with the domain.

Message: Inconsistent value for ARMCD
Description: A value for Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) must have a unique value for Description of Planned Arm (ARM) with the domain.

Message: Non-unique value for TSSEQ variable within TSPARMCD
Description: Sequence Number (TSSEQ) must have a unique value for a given value of Trial Summary Parameter Short Name (TSPARMCD) within the domain.

Message: --CAT value is redundant with other variable values
Description: Value of Category (--CAT) should not be identical to that in Domain Abbreviation (DOMAIN); Reported Term (--TERM); Name of Measurement, Test, or Examination (--TESTCD); Name of Treatment (--TRT); Standardized Coded Term (--DECOD); Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS).

Message: --SCAT value is redundant with other variable values
Description: Value of Subcategory (--SCAT) should not be identical to that in Domain Abbreviation (DOMAIN); Reported Term (--TERM); Name of Measurement, Test, or Examination (--TESTCD); Name of Treatment (--TRT); Standardized Coded Term (--DECOD); Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS).

Message: Values for --CAT and --SCAT are identical
Description: Values of Category (--CAT) and Subcategory (--SCAT) variables should not be identical.

Message: Time point for non-occurred event or intervention is provided
Description: Value of Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF) or End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF) should not be populated when an event or intervention is marked as not occurred (--OCCUR='N').

Message: Inconsistent value for --TESTCD within --TEST
Description: All values of Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD) should be the same for a given value of Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST).

Message: Both --DOSE and --DOSTXT values are populated
Description: Only one of Dose (--DOSE) or Dose Description (--DOSTXT) variables must be populated on the same record.

Message: Invalid value for QLABEL
Description: Qualifier Variable Label (QLABEL) value may have up to 40 characters.

Message: Non-unique value for ETCD within ELEMENT
Description: Element Code (ETCD) must have a unique value for a given value of Description of Element (ELEMENT) within the domain.

Message: Unexpected value for IDVAR/IDVARVAL
Description: Both Identifying Variable (IDVAR) and Identifying Variable Value (IDVARVAL) should not be populated when relating information to the Demographics (DM) domain.

Message: Non-unique value for TAETORD within ARMCD
Description: Order of Element within Arm (TAETORD) must have a unique value for a given value of Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) within the domain.

Message: Dataset is not present in define.xml
Description: Datasets included in study data must be described in the data definition document (define.xml).

Message: Duplicate ETCD value
Description: The value of Element Code (ETCD) variable must be unique within Trial Elements (TE) domain.

Message: Missing RDOMAIN value when IDVAR is populated
Description: Value of Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN) variable must be populated when value of Identifying Variable (IDVAR) variable is populated.

Message: IDVARVAL value is populated when RELTYPE values is populated
Description: Variable Value (IDVARVAL) variable value should not be populated when Relationship Type (RELTYPE) variable value is populated.

Message: USUBJID value is populated when RELTYPE values is populated
Description: Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variable value should not be populated when Relationship Type (RELTYPE) variable value is populated.

Message: Duplicate ELEMENT value
Description: The value of Element (Description of Element) variable must be unique within Trial Elements (TE) domain.

Message: Inconsistent value for --PARM within --PARMCD
Description: All values of a Parameter (--PARM) variables should be the same for a given value of a Parameter Short Name (--PARMCD) variables.

Message: Inconsistent value for --PARMCD within --PARM
Description: All values of a Parameter Short Name (--PARMCD) variables should be the same for a given value of a Parameter (--PARM) variables.

Message: Dataset is greater than 5 GB in size
Description: Datasets greater than 5 gigabytes (GB) in size should be split into smaller datasets no larger than 5 GB.

Message: Missing IDVAR value when RDOMAIN value is provided
Description: Value of Identifying Variable (IDVAR) variable must be populated when Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN) variable value is provided, with the only exception of 'DM' value for RDOMAIN.

Message: Variable prohibited for use in SDTM
Description: Variables described in IG as inappropriate for usage must be not included in the dataset.

Message: Model Permissible variable added into standard domain
Description: SDTM model variable may be added into standard domains according to its domain general class, if there are no restrictions on their usage specified in IG.

Message: Variable is in wrong order within domain
Description: The order of variables should reflect the order of the variables in the SDTM Model. Variables for the three general observation classes must be ordered with Identifiers first, followed by the Topic, Qualifier, and Timing variables. Within each role, variables must be ordered as shown in SDTM: Tables 2.2.1, 2.2.2, 2.2.3, 2.2.4, and 2.2.5.

Message: Variable length is too long for actual data
Description: Variable length should be assigned based on actual stored data to minimize file size. Datasets should be re-sized to the maximum length of actual data used prior to splitting.

Message: Missing --DY variable when --DTC variable is present
Description: Collection Study Day (--DY) variable should be included into dataset when Collection Study Date/Time (--DTC) variable is present.

Message: --DY variable value is not populated
Description: Collection Study Day (--DY) variable value should be populated when Collection Study Date/Time (--DTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both include complete date part.

Message: --DY variable value is imputed
Description: Collection Study Day (--DY) variable value should not be imputed. It may be only populated when both Collection Study Date/Time (--DTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided and both include complete date part.

Message: Incorrect value for --DY variable
Description: Collection Study Day (--DY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --DY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) +1 if --DTC is on or after RFSTDTC; --DY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --DTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Message: Missing --STDY variable when --STDTC variable is present
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable should be included into dataset when Start Study Date/Time (--STDTC) variable is present.

Message: --STDY variable value is not populated
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable value should be populated when Start Study Date (--STDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both include complete date part.

Message: --STDY variable value is imputed
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable value should not be imputed. It may be only populated when both Start Study Date/Time (--STDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both include complete date part.

Message: Incorrect value for --STDY variable
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --STDY = (date portion of --STDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) +1 if --STDTC is on or after RFSTDTC; --STDY = (date portion of --STDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --STDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Message: Missing --ENDY variable when --ENDTC variable is present
Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable should be included into dataset when End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) variable is present.

Message: --ENDY variable value is not populated
Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable value should be populated when End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both include complete date part.

Message: --ENDY variable value is imputed
Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable value should not be imputed. It may be only populated when both End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both include complete date part.

Message: Incorrect value for --ENDY variable
Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --ENDY = (date portion of --ENDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) +1 if --ENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC; --ENDY = (date portion of --ENDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --ENDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Message: Invalid dataset name for split domain
Description: Split datasets must not have the name of original domain. E.g., lbhm.xpt is a valid name when lb.xpt is not a valid dataset name for split domain.

Message: High risk of truncated value for --TERM variable
Description: SAS v5 export format has a limitation on variables length up to 200 characters. If the collected value was more than 200 characters, then SUPPQUAL dataset should be used to store additional 200+ characters. Variable QNAM should have --TERM1, ---TERM2, etc. values for those records. Value splitting should be performed between words or numbers. See SDTM IG #4.1.5.3.2 for details. This risk-assessment check is triggered based on assumption that if original value was truncated, then the actual data value length is exactly 200 characters.

Message: Missing --CAT value when --SCAT value is populated
Description: Value for Category (--CAT) variable should be populated when value for Subcategory (--SCAT) variable is populated.

Message: Missing --CAT variable when --SCAT variable is present
Description: Category (--CAT) variable should be included into dataset when Subcategory (--SCAT) variable is present.

Message: Missing --ENTPT variable when --ENRTPT variable is present
Description: End Reference Time Point (--ENTPT) variable must be included into the domain when End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) variable is present.

Message: Missing --ENRTPT variable when --ENTPT variable is present
Description: End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) variable must be included into the domain when End Relative Time Point (--ENTPT) variable is present.

Message: Missing --STTPT variable when --STRTPT variable is present
Description: Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) variable must be included into the domain when Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) variable is present.

Message: Missing --STRTPT variable when --STTPT variable is present
Description: Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) variable must be included into the domain when Start Relative Time Point (--STTPT) variable is present.

Message: Missing EX dataset
Description: Exposure (EX) dataset should be included in every submission.

Message: Missing DS dataset
Description: Disposition (DS) dataset should be included in every submission.

Message: Missing SE dataset
Description: Subject Elements (SE) dataset should be included in every submission.

Message: Missing TA dataset
Description: Trial Arms (TA) dataset should be included in every submission.

Message: Missing TE dataset
Description: Trial Elements (TE) dataset should be included in every submission.

Message: Missing TS dataset
Description: Trial Summary (TS) dataset must be included in every submission.

Message: Inconsistent variable length within split datasets
Description: Split datasets should have matching variable lengths for future mergers. Datasets should be resized to the maximum length used prior to splitting.

Message: Duplicate records
Description: The structure of Findings class domains should be one record per Finding Result per subject. No Finding Result with the same Test Short Name (--TESTCD) and the same Qualifier variables at the same timepoint for the same Subject (USUBJID) are expected.

Message: Neither --STDTC, --DTC nor --STDY are populated
Description: At least one value of three variables Start Date/Time (--STDTC), Collection Date/Time (--DTC) or Start Study Day (--STDY) should be populated.

Message: Inappropriate usage of variables in CO domain when comment is a child record of another domain
Description: In the Comments (CO) domain, the following Identifier and Timing variables are Permissible and may be populated as appropriate when comments are not related to other domain records (i.e., RDOMAIN and IDVAR variable values are not populated): COGRPID, COREFID, COSPID, VISIT, VISITNUM, VISITDY, TAETORD, CODY, COTPT, COTPTNUM, COELTM, COTPTREF, CORFTDTC.

Message: Comments in SUPPQUAL domain
Description: Comments should be stored in Comments (CO) domain, rather than be put into Supplemental Qualifier (SUPP--) domains.

Message: Neither AGE nor AGETXT values are populated
Description: Value for Age (AGE) or Age Range (AGETXT) variables should be populated for all subjects. The only exception for SDTM is for Screen Failures (ARMCD=SCRNFAIL) and Not Assigned (ARMCD=NOTASSGN) subjects, or subjects with ARMCD=null. There are no exceptions for SEND.

Message: Missing value for --STRESN
Description: Standardized Result in Numeric Format (--STRESN) variable value should be populated when Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value represents a numeric value.

Message: --ORRES value is populated when --STAT is 'NOT DONE'
Description: Value of Original Result (--ORRES) variable is expected to be missing when observation was not performed (Status (--STAT) is 'NOT DONE').

Message: Missing value for --REASND when --STAT is 'NOT DONE'
Description: Value of Reason Not Done (--REASND) variable should be populated when Status (--STAT) variable value is 'NOT DONE'.

Message: Invalid value for RELTYPE variable
Description: Relationship Type (RELTYPE) variable values should be populated with terms 'ONE', 'MANY' when Related Records (RELREC) dataset is used to identify relationships between datasets.

Message: Neither AGE nor AGETXT variables are present
Description: At least one of Age (AGE) or Age Text (AGETXT) variables should be included into Demographics (DM) domain.

Message: Inconsistent value for QNAM within QLABEL
Description: All values of Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM) should be the same for a given value of Qualifier Variable Label (QLABEL).

Message: Missing --STRESC value for Baseline record
Description: A Standard Result value (--STRESC) is expected to be populated for Baseline records (--BLFL='Y').

Message: Negative value of Study Day variable
Description: Study Day variables (*DY) value should not be negative in Exposure (EX) and Exposure As Collected (EC) datasets.

Message: Expected variable with missing value for all records
Description: Expected variables may contain some null values, but in most cases will not contain null values for every record. When no data has been collected for an Expected variable, however, a null column must still be included in the dataset, and a comment must be included in the define.xml to state that data was not collected.

Message: Duplicate records in domain
Description: The structure of Events class domains should be one record per Event per subject. No Events with the same Collected Term (--TERM), Decoded Term (--DECOD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Occurrence (--OCCUR), Location (--LOC), Laterality (--LAT), Directionality (--DIR), Severity (--SEV), Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR), Visit Number (VISITNUM), Visit Day (VISITDY), and Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) values for the same Subject (USUBJID) and the same Start Date (--STDTC) are expected.

Message: EXSTDTC date is before RFXSTDTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) variable value must be greater than or equal to Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC).

Message: EXSTDTC date is after RFXENDTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).

Message: EXENDTC date is after RFXENDTC
Description: End Date/Time of Treatment (EXENDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).

Message: RFXSTDTC date is after RFXENDTC
Description: Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).

Message: Missing value for RFXENDTC when RFXSTDTC is provided
Description: Value for Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC) variable must be populated when Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable value is provided.

Message: --STRESN does not equal --STRESC
Description: Standardized Result in Numeric Format (--STRESN) variable value should be equal Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value when Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value represents a numeric value.

Message: Variable value not found in user-defined codelist when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable value must be populated with terms from user-defined value level codelist as specified in define.xml file.

Message: Variable value is null when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable value must be populated when value level attribute Mandatory='Yes' as specified in define.xml file.

Message: Variable datatype is not %Variable.@Clause.DataType% when value-level condition occurs
Description: Value level datatype must match the datatype described in define.xml.

Message: Variable value is longer than defined max length %Variable.@Clause.Length% when value-level condition occurs
Description: Value level length must not exceed the length as specified define.xml.

Message: Missing --TPT variable when --TPTNUM variable is present
Description: Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable must be included into the domain when Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable is present.

Message: Missing --TPTREF variable when --RFTDTC variable is present
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable must be included into the domain when Date/Time of Reference Point (--RFTDTC) variable is present.

Message: Missing --TPTREF variable when --ELTM variable is present
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable must be included into the domain when Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref (--ELTM) variable is present.

Message: Missing --TPTNUM variable when --TPT variable is present
Description: Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable must be included into the domain when Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable is present.

Message: --VAMTU value is populated when --TRTV is null
Description: Treatment Vehicle Amount Units (--VAMTU) value must be null when Treatment Vehicle Amount (--TRTV) value is null.

Message: Invalid value for SETCD exceeding 8 characters
Description: The value of Set Code (SETCD) should be no more than 8 characters in length.

Message: ETCD equals 'UNPLAN' when SEUPDES is null
Description: When the Description of Unplanned Element (SEUPDES) is not populated, the Element Code (ETCD) should not be equal to 'UNPLAN'.

Message: The combination of ELEMENT, TESTRL TEENRL, and TEDUR is not unique for each ETCD
Description: The combination of Description of Element (ELEMENT), Rule for Start of Element (TESTRL), Rule for End of Element (TEENRL), and Planned Duration of Element (TEDUR) should be unique for each Element Code (ETCD).

Message: No timing variables are present in dataset
Description: All domains based on the general observation classes (Interventions, Events, Findings) should have at least one Timing variable present.

Message: Missing value for --STRESC when --STAT is null
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Format (--STRESC) value should not be null when Completion Status (--STAT) value is null.

Message: Define.xml/dataset variable label mismatch
Description: Variable Label in define.xml must match variable Label in dataset.

Message: Define.xml/dataset description mismatch
Description: Dataset Description in define.xml must match dataset Description.

Message: --DY is after --ENDY
Description: Study Day of Observation (--DY) must be less or equal to Study Day of End of Observation (--ENDY).

Message: --STDTC is after --DTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Event, Exposure (--STDTC) must be less or equal to Date/Time of Collection(--DTC).

Message: Missing value for RFXSTDTC when RFXENDTC is provided
Description: Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable must be populated when Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC)variable value is provided.

Message: Missing value for RFXSTDTC when subject is treated
Description: Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable must be populated when subject is treated (ACTARMCD is not 'SCRNFAIL', 'NOTTRT', 'NOTASSGN', or null).

Message: Missing values for --STINT and --ENINT variables when --TEST references 'T1 to T2'
Description: Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) and Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) variables should be present and populated when Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST) is over a time interval, 'T1 to T2', where 'T1' is represented by the value in --STINT and 'T2' is represented by the value in --ENINT.

Message: Inconsistent STUDYID
Description: Study Identifier (STUDYID) values should be consistent for all subjects in the Demographics (DM) domain for one study.

Message: Missing value for --ENINT when --STINT is provided
Description: Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) should not be null when Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --STINT when --ENINT is provided
Description: Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) should not be null when Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) is populated.

Message: Duplicate records in domain
Description: The structure of Interventions class domains should be one record per Intervention Episode per subject. No Interventions with the same Treatment (--TRT), Decoded Term (--DECOD), Mood (--MOOD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Route (--ROUTE), Location (--LOC) and Treatment Vehicle (--TRTV) values for the same Subject (USUBJID) with the same Start Date (--STDTC), Planned Time Point Name (--TPT), and Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) are expected.

Message: --STRESC does not equal --ORRES when --STRESU is equal to --ORRESU
Description: Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value should be equal to Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) variable value when variable values are numeric and Standard Units (--STRESU) and Original Units (--ORRESU) are populated with the same units or are null.

Message: ARMCD value is not present in DM
Description: Arm Code (ARMCD) values defined in Trial Arms (TA) should be assigned to at least one subject (USUBJID) in Demographics (DM).

Message: ETCD value does not present in TA
Description: Element Code (ETCD) values defined in Trial Elements (TE) should be assigned for at least one Arm Code (ARMCD) in Trial Arms (Trial Arms).

Message: ETCD value does not present in SE
Description: Element Code (ETCD) values defined in Trial Elements (TE) should be assigned to at least one subject (USUBJID) in Subject Elements (SE).

Message: Exposure start date is after the latest Disposition date
Description: Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC). Investigator should provide a date of study discontinuation for each subject in Disposition (DS) domain. If the study is ongoing, Parameter Value (TSVAL) for the 'ONGOSIND/Ongoing Study Indicator' parameter should be set to 'Y' in the Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: --STRESN is populated when --STRESC value is not numeric
Description: Standardized Result in Numeric Format (--STRESN) variable value should be null when Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value does not represent a numeric value, (e.g., 'BLQ', value contains '<' or '>', etc.).

Message: Missing --ENINT variable when --STINT variable is present
Description: Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) variable must be included in the domain when Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) variable is present.

Message: Missing --STINT variable when --ENINT variable is present
Description: Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) variable must be included in the domain when Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) variable is present.

Message: Negative value for --VAMT
Description: Non-missing Treatment Vehicle Amount (--VAMT) value must be greater than or equal to 0.

Message: Invalid value for Dataset Name
Description: Dataset Name (DATASET) should follow limitations of SAS XPORT format v5. It should not exceed 8 characters and cannot contain characters other than letters in upper case, numbers, or underscores.

Message: Invalid value for Variable Name
Description: Variable Name should follow limitations of SAS XPORT format v5. It should not exceed 8 characters and cannot contain characters other than letters in upper case, numbers, or underscores. It cannot start with a number.

Message: Missing values for both --VAL and --VALNF
Description: Value for Parameter Value (--VAL) variable must be populated. --VAL can only be null when Parameter Null Flavor (--VALNF) variable value is populated.

Message: Both --VAL and --VALNF variables are populated
Description: Value for Parameter Null Flavor (--VALNF) variable should be null when Parameter Value (--VAL) variable value can be populated.

Message: Invalid value for AGETXT
Description: Age Range (AGETXT) variable values should be populated with 'number-number' format.

Message: Both AGE and AGETXT variables values are populated
Description: Age (AGE) and Age Range (AGETXT) variables should never both be populated for the same subject.

Message: Missing values for both AGE and AGETXT when AGEU is provided
Description: Either of Age (AGE) or Age Range (AGETXT) variable values should be provided when Age Units (AGEU) are populated.

Message: Missing value for AGEU when AGE or AGETXT is populated
Description: Age Units (AGEU) variable values should be provided when Age (AGE) or Age Range (AGETXT) variables values are populated.

Message: AGE is not provided
Description: Age (AGE) variable values should be provided when Date/Time of Birth (BRTHDTC) variable values are populated.

Message: Redundant values for USUBJID and POOLID
Description: Only one of the Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) or Pool Identifier (POOLID) variables values may be populated, not both.

Message: Missing value for --VAMT when --VAMTU is populated
Description: Treatment Vehicle Amount (--VAMT) should not be null when Treatment Vehicle Amount Units (--VAMTU) is populated.

Message: Dataset class not recognized
Description: The structure for custom dataset should be based on one of the general observation classes (EVENTS, FINDINGS, INTERVENTIONS) defined by the SDTM model.

Message: Missing TX dataset
Description: Trial Sets (TX) dataset should be included in every submission.

Message: Missing values for both --DTC and --DY variables
Description: Date/Time of Observation (--DTC) or Study Day of Observation (--DY) should be populated in the Findings observation class where data are usually collected at multiple study days.

Message: Missing value for --TPTREF when --RFTDTC is provided
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable values should be provided when Date/Time of Reference Time Point (--RFTDTC) variable values are populated.

Message: SEND/dataset variable type mismatch
Description: Variable Data Types in the dataset should match the variable data types described in SEND IG and SDTM Model.

Message: SEND Required variable not found
Description: Variables described in SEND IG as Required must be included in the dataset.

Message: SEND Expected variable not found
Description: Variables described in SEND IG as Expected should be included in the dataset.

Message: SEND/dataset variable label mismatch
Description: Variable Label in the dataset should match the variable label described in SEND IG. When creating a new domain Variable Labels could be adjusted as appropriate to properly convey the meaning in the context of the data being submitted.

Message: No Exposure record found for subject
Description: All Demographics (DM) subjects (USUBJID) participating in a study that includes investigational product should have at least one record in the Exposure (EX) domain, except for subjects where ARMCD is not populated.

Message: TFDETECT is after DSSTDY
Description: Time in Days to Detection of Tumor (TFDETECT) should be less than or equal to the Study Day of Disposition of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDY).

Message: Variable which can be used only in SDTM
Description: Variables designed only for SDTM human studies must be not included in the SEND dataset.

Message: Inconsistent value for --ELTM within --TPT, --TPTREF, --CAT and/or --SCAT
Description: All values of Planned Elapsed Time (--ELTM) variable should be the same for a given value of Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable, Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) and if present, Category and/or Subcategory (--CAT/--SCAT).

Message: Inconsistent value for --TPT within --TPTNUM, --NOMDY, --CAT and/or --SCAT
Description: All values of Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable should be the same for a given value of Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable. Uniqueness for these time points is determined by a combination of the Nominal Study Day for tabulations (--NOMDY), and, if present, Category and/or Subcategory (--CAT/--SCAT).

Message: Inconsistent value for --TPTNUM within --TPT, --NOMDY, --CAT and/or --SCAT
Description: All values of Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable should be the same for a given value of Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable. Uniqueness for these time points is determined by a combination of the Nominal Study Day for tabulations (--NOMDY), and, if present, Category and/or Subcategory (--CAT/--SCAT).

Message: EXSTDTC date is before EXPSTDTC in TS domain
Description: Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) variable value must be greater than or equal to Date/Time of Experimental Start Date (EXPSTDTC) in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: EXSTDTC date is after EXPENDTC in TS domain
Description: Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Experimental End Date (EXPENDTC) in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: EXENDTC date is before EXPSTDTC in TS domain
Description: End Date/Time of Treatment (EXENDTC) variable value must be greater than or equal to Date/Time of Experimental Start Date (EXPSTDTC) in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: EXENDTC date is after EXPENDTC in TS domain
Description: End Date/Time of Treatment (EXENDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Experimental End Date (EXPENDTC) in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: EXSTDTC date is before RFSTDTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) variable value must be greater than or equal to Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC).

Message: Missing PLANMSUB Trial Set Parameter within SETCD
Description: 'Planned Number of Male Subjects' (PLANMSUB) records should be populated for each SETCD in Trial Sets (TX) domain.

Message: Missing PLANFSUB Trial Set Parameter within SETCD
Description: 'Planned Number of Female Subjects' (PLANFSUB) records should be populated for each SETCD in Trial Sets (TX) domain.

Message: Missing both AGE and AGETXT Trial Summary Parameters
Description: 'Age' (AGE) or 'Age Text' (AGETXT) records should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing AGEU Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Age Unit' (AGEU) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing SDESIGN Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Study Design' (SDESIGN) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing DOSDUR Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Dosing Duration' (DOSDUR) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing EXPENDTC Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Experimental End Date' (EXPENDTC) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing EXPSTDTC Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Experimental Start Date' (EXPSTDTC) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing GLPTYP Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Good Laboratory Practice Type' (GLPTYP) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing ROUTE Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Route of Administration' (ROUTE) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing SNDIGVER Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'SEND Implementation Guide Version' (SNDIGVER) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing SNDCTVER Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'SEND Control Terminology Version' (SNDCTVER) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing SPECIES Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Species' (SPECIES) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing SPLRNAM Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Test Subject Supplier' (SPLRNAM) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing SPREFID Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Sponsor's Reference ID' (SPREFID) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing SSPONSOR Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Sponsoring Organization' (SSPONSOR) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing STCAT Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Study Category' (STCAT) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing STDIR Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Study Director' (STDIR) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing STRAIN Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Strain/Substrain' (STRAIN) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing STSTDTC Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Study Start Date' (STSTDTC) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing STITLE Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Study Title' (STITLE) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing SSTYP Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Study Type' (SSTYP) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing TRT Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Investigational Therapy or Treatment' (TRT) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing TFCNTRY Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Test Facility Country' (TFCNTRY) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing TSTFLOC Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Test Facility Location' (TSTFLOC) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing TSTFNAM Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Test Facility Name' (TSTFNAM) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing TRMSAC Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Time to Terminal Sacrifice' (TRMSAC) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing TRTCAS Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Primary Treatment CAS Registry Number' (TRTCAS) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing TRTV Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Treatment Vehicle' (TRTV) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing --RESCAT value when --STRESC is not 'NORMAL', 'UNREMARKABLE', or null (--STAT = 'NOT DONE')
Description: Result Category (--RESCAT) should be populated for all abnormal findings, i.e. when Result or Finding in Standard Format (--STRESC) has a value other than 'NORMAL', 'UNREMARKABLE' or missing (Completion Status (--STAT) = 'NOT DONE').

Message: --STRESC/--RESCAT mismatch when --RESCAT = 'BENIGN', 'MALIGNANT' or 'UNDETERMINED'
Description: Result or Finding in Standard Format (--STRESC) values from (NEOPLASM) CT codelist should align with the malignancy status in Result Category (--RESCAT) when --RESCAT = 'BENIGN', 'MALIGNANT' or 'UNDETERMINED'.

Message: Inconsistent value for SET within SETCD
Description: All values of Set Description (SET) should be the same for a given value of Set Code (SETCD).

Message: Inconsistent value for SETCD within SET
Description: All values of Set Code (SETCD) should be the same for a given value of Set Description (SET).

Message: Invalid TXVAL for ARMCD
Description: Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) values in TXVAL (TXPARMCD = 'ARMCD') should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset.

Message: --RESCAT should not be populated when --STRESC is 'NORMAL', 'UNREMARKABLE', or null (--STAT = 'NOT DONE')
Description: Result Category (--RESCAT) should not be populated when Result or Finding in Standard Format (--STRESC) is 'NORMAL', 'UNREMARKABLE' or missing (Completion Status (--STAT) = 'NOT DONE').

Message: No record for --CALCN when --STRESC is below LOQ
Description: A numeric interpretation for calculations record (QNAM.PCCALCN) should be included in SUPPPC when the Result or Finding in Standard Format (PCSTRESC) is below the limit of quantification ('BLQ' or 'BQL') per guidance in the FDA Technical Conformance Guide.

Message: Multiple SNDIGVER records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for the 'SNDIGVER' parameter.

Message: Multiple SNDCTVER records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for the 'SNDCTVER' parameter.

Message: Value from NULLFLAV codelist is populated in TSVAL
Description: Values from the Null Flavor Reason (NULLFLAV) codelist should be populated in Parameter Null Flavor (TSVALNF) rather than Parameter Value (TSVAL) in the Trial Summary (TS) domain when using SENDIG v3.1 and later.

Message: Value from NY codelist is populated in TSVAL when TSPARMCD = 'GLPTYP'
Description: Values from the No Yes Response (NY) codelist should not be populated in Parameter Value (TSVAL) when TSPARMCD = 'GLPTYP' (Good Laboratory Practice Type) in the Trial Summary (TS) domain. The NY codelist should be used to populate TSVAL when TSPARMCD = 'GLPFL' (GLP Flag) and not when TSPARMCD = 'GLPTYP'.

Message: --RESCAT value is redundant with other variable values
Description: Value of Result Category (--RESCAT) should not be identical to that in Test Name (--TEST); Category (--CAT); and/or Subcategory (--SCAT).

Message: --ENDTC is after the latest Disposition date
Description: End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC) for an animal's live-phase findings should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC).

Message: --DTC is after the latest Disposition date
Description: Date/Time of Observation (--DTC) for an animal's live-phase findings should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC).

Message: Missing value for --SPEC when --TESTCD equals 'GROSPATH'
Description: Specimen Material Type (MASPEC) is required to be populated when Macroscopic Examination Short Name (MATESTCD)/Macroscopic Examination Name (MATEST) = 'GROSPATH'/'Gross Pathological Observation'.

Message: --SPEC variable is populated when --TESTCD equals 'CLSFUP'
Description: Specimen Material Type (MASPEC) should be null when Macroscopic Examination Short Name (MATESTCD)/Macroscopic Examination Name (MATEST) = 'CLSFUP'/'Clinical Signs Follow-up'.

Message: --STRESC is the same as --ORRES when --STRESC is not 'NORMAL' or 'UNREMARKABLE' and a Qualifier variable is populated
Description: Result or Finding in Standard Format (--STRESC) should be populated with the base observation without modifiers. Other relevant components of the Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) finding must be parsed into one or more Qualifier variables and the Supplemental Qualifier --RESMOD.

Message: Missing TSNAM Trial Summary Parameter when TSCNTRY and/or TSLOC Parameters are provided
Description: 'Test Site Name' (TSNAM) record should be provided in the Trial Summary (TS) domain when records for 'Test Site Country' (TSCNTRY) and/or 'Test Site Location' (TSLOC) are present.

Message: --DTC is before the latest Disposition date
Description: Date/Time of Collection (--DTC) variable value must be greater than or equal to Start Date/Time of latest Disposition (DSSTDTC) for post-mortem Findings domains: Death Diagnosis and Details (DD), Macroscopic Findings (MA), Microscopic Findings (MI), Organ Measurements (OM), Tumor Findings (TF).

Message: Negative value for --STRESN when --EXCLFL is not populated
Description: The value of Standardized Result in Numeric Format (--STRESN) cannot be less than 0 when the record is not excluded from analysis, i.e., Exclude from Statistics (--EXCLFL) is not 'Y'. This applies for the following domains in SEND: BW, FM, FW, LB, OM, PC, PY, RE, VS.

Message: Missing STRPSTAT Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Study Report Status' (STRPSTAT) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: No record in DD domain for unscheduled death
Description: For subjects that have a disposition status in the Disposition (DS) domain that indicates an unscheduled death, the cause of death should be captured in the Death Diagnosis and Details (DD) domain. Standardized Disposition Term (DSDECOD) values for unscheduled death include ACCIDENTAL DEATH, FOUND DEAD, MISSING, MORIBUND SACRIFICE, or NON-MORIBUND SACRIFICE. For SEND v3.1 and later, Unscheduled Flag (DSUSCHFL) should also be set to 'Y'.

Message: Unscheduled flag is populated for scheduled death
Description: For subjects that have a disposition status in the Disposition (DS) domain that indicates a scheduled death, the Unscheduled Flag (DSUSCHFL) should not be populated. Standardized Disposition Term (DSDECOD) values for scheduled death include: INTERIM SACRIFICE, TERMINAL SACRIFICE, RECOVERY SACRIFICE, and REMOVED FROM STUDY ALIVE.

Message: --DY value does not equal DSSTDY value
Description: For a specimen collected or observed post mortem, the Study Day (--DY) variable value should be the same as the Study Day of Disposition (DSSTDY) variable value in the Disposition (DS) domain.

Message: --DY value when BWTESTCD = 'TERMBW' does not equal DSSTDY value
Description: For terminal body weight measurements (BWTESTCD/BWTEST = 'TERMBW'/'Terminal Body Weight'), the Study Day Animal Weighed (BWDY) variable value should be the same as the Study Day of Disposition (DSSTDY) variable value in the Disposition (DS) domain.

Message: Multiple SDESIGN records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for the 'SDESIGN' parameter.

Message: Multiple STCAT records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for the 'STCAT' parameter.

Message: Multiple SSTYP records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for the 'SSTYP' parameter.

Message: Multiple STDIR records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for the 'STDIR' parameter.

Message: --DTC does not equal DSSTDTC
Description: Date/Time of Collection (--DTC) variable value must be equal to Start Date/Time of latest Disposition (DSSTDTC) for post-mortem findings in the Macroscopic Findings (MA), Microscopic Findings (MI), and Tumor Findings (TF) domains.

Message: variable length exceeds 200 characters
Description: Due to SAS v5 transport file limitations, variables cannot have a length that is greater than 200 characters. For SEND data, this results in loading errors into regulatory nonclinical review tools. The SENDIG should be followed in how to split long character strings appropriately.

Message: Missing value for PCLLOQ when PCSTRESC is 'BLQ' or 'BQL'
Description: When a measurement is identified as being below a limit of quantification threshold in Standardized Result in Character Format (PCSTRESC), Lower Limit of Quantitation (PCLLOQ) should be populated.

Message: Duplicate value for PCTPTREF for the same USUBJID (or POOLID) when PCNOMDY value is different
Description: Time Point Reference (PCTPTREF) must identify a unique dose. Ambiguous references such as 'Most recent dose' should be avoided; it is recommended that Time Point Reference (PCTPTREF) include both the Nominal Study Day for Tabulations (PCNOMDY) and the time point description in order (e.g., “Day 1, Dose 1” and “Day 1, Dose 2” for twice daily dosing).

Message: PCELTM is not 'PT0H' for pre-dose sampling
Description: Specimen concentrations (e.g., plasma) used to calculate a time concentration profile with a pre-dose sample should have Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref (PCELTM) populated with 'PT0H'. A negative elapsed time would lead to an incorrect area under the curve.

Message: Missing values for required timing variables: --NOMDY, --ELTM, and --TPTREF
Description: For PC records contributing to a time concentration profile, PCNOMDY, PCELTM and PCTPTREF must be present and populated. These are the required timing variables for identification of the day on which group summaries (Group Means and Incidences) are calculated for pharmacokinetic concentrations.

Message: Duplicate USUBJID within a POOLID
Description: There should be only one record per subject (USUBJID) within Pool Identifier (POOLID) in the Pool Definition (POOLDEF) domain.

Message: Unscheduled flag is not populated for unscheduled death
Description: For subjects that have a disposition status in the Disposition (DS) domain that indicates an unscheduled death, the Unscheduled Flag (DSUSCHFL) should be set to 'Y'. Standardized Disposition Term (DSDECOD) values for unscheduled death include: ACCIDENTAL DEATH, FOUND DEAD, MISSING, MORIBUND SACRIFICE, or NON-MORIBUND SACRIFICE.

Message: --STRESC value is not 'UNREMARKABLE' when no findings are present
Description: If the examination was completed and there were no findings populated in Result or Finding as Collected (--ORRES), the value must be 'UNREMARKABLE' in Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) when using SEND v3.1 or later.

Message: --STRESC value is not 'NORMAL' when no findings are present
Description: If the examination was completed and there were no findings populated in Result or Finding as Collected (--ORRES), the value must be 'NORMAL' in Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) when using SEND v3.0 (MA, MI, CL) or SEND v3.1 or later (CL only).

Message: Record present in DD domain for scheduled death
Description: For subjects that have a disposition status in the Disposition (DS) domain that indicates a scheduled death, no records should be present in the Death Diagnosis and Details (DD) domain. Standardized Disposition Term (DSDECOD) values for scheduled death include: INTERIM SACRIFICE, TERMINAL SACRIFICE, RECOVERY SACRIFICE, and REMOVED FROM STUDY ALIVE.

Message: Missing ARMCD Trial Set Parameter within SETCD
Description: 'Arm Code' (ARMCD) records should be populated for each SETCD in Trial Sets (TX) domain.

Message: Missing SPGRPCD Trial Set Parameter within SETCD
Description: 'Sponsor-Defined Group Code' (SPGRPCD) records should be populated for each SETCD in Trial Sets (TX) domain.

Message: Missing GRPLBL Trial Set Parameter within SETCD
Description: 'Group Label' (GRPLBL) records should be populated for each SETCD in Trial Sets (TX) domain.

Message: Missing TRTDOS Trial Set Parameter within SETCD
Description: 'Dose Level' (TRTDOS) records should be populated for each SETCD in Trial Sets (TX) domain.

Message: Missing TRTDOSU Trial Set Parameter within SETCD
Description: 'Dose Units' (TRTDOSU) records should be populated for each SETCD in Trial Sets (TX) domain.

Message: Missing values for all required set(s) of timing variables: VISITDY, --STDY, or --NOMDY
Description: At least one of these variables or sets of variables must be present and populated in DS: (VISITDY, DSSTDY, or DSNOMDY). These are the required timing variables for identification of the day on which group summaries (Group Means and Incidences) are calculated for post mortem data.

Message: Missing values for all required set(s) of timing variables: VISITDY, --DY or --NOMDY
Description: At least one of the these variables or sets of variables should be populated: VISITDY, --DY, or --NOMDY. These are the Required timing variables for identification of the day on which group summaries (Group Means and Incidences) are calculated.

Message: Missing values for all required timing variables: --DY & --ENDY
Description: These variables must be populated: --DY and --ENDY. These are the required timing variables for identification of the day on which group summaries (Group Means and Incidences) are calculated for data associated with a time interval.

Message: Value for --STRESC is populated when --STAT is 'NOT DONE'
Description: Status (--STAT) should be null when Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC ) is provided.

Message: Invalid SETCD
Description: Set Code (SETCD) values should match entries in the Trial Sets (TX) dataset.

Message: Invalid POOLID
Description: Pool ID (POOLID) values should match entries in the Pool Definition (POOLDEF) dataset.

Message: No Trial Set with TCNTRL Parameter
Description: 'Control Type' (TCNTRL) record should be populated in Trial Sets (TX) domain. (There must be a record with TXPARMCD = TCNTRL within a set if the study has a control).

Message: Duplicate TXPARMCD within a SETCD
Description: The value of Parameter Code (TXPARMCD) variable must be unique for each Trial Set (SETCD) within the Trial Sets (TX) domain.

Message: Missing values for all required set(s) of timing variables: VISITDY or --NOMDY
Description: At least one of these variables or sets of variables must be present and populated in PP: VISITDY or PPNOMDY. These are the required timing variables for identification of the day on which group summaries (Group Means and Incidences) are calculated for pharmacokinetic parameters.

Message: No baseline flag record in Domain for subject
Description: All subjects should have at least one baseline observation (--BLFL = 'Y') in EG, LB, and VS domains.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for SLENGTH
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g., P80Y) or null when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD='SLENGTH'.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for SPLANSUB
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL must be numeric when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD = 'SPLANSUB'.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for PLANFSUB
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL must be numeric when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD = 'PLANFSUB'.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for PLANMSUB
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL must be numeric when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD = 'PLANMSUB'.

Message: Invalid TSVAL value for STSTDTC
Description: TSVAL variable value must be in ISO 8601 format when TSPARMCD='STSTDTC'.

Message: Incomplete date for study start date
Description: TSVAL variable value must be in ISO 8601 format and include at least full date, when TSPARMCD='STSTDTC'.

Message: Invalid TSVAL value for STENDTC
Description: TSVAL variable value must be in ISO 8601 format when TSPARMCD='STENDTC'.

Message: Missing SPLANSUB Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Planned Number of Subjects' (SPLANSUB) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing STENDTC Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Study End Date' (STENDTC) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing DOSENDTC Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'End Date/Time of Dose Interval' (DOSENDTC) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing DOSSTDTC Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Start Date/Time of Dose Interval' (DOSSTDTC) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing GLPFL Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Good Laboratory Practice Flag' (GLPFL) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing PCLASS Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Pharmacologic Class' (PCLASS) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing PDOSFRQ Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Planned Dose Frequency' (PDOSFRQ) record should be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing SEXPOP Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Sex of Participants' (SEXPOP) record must be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Missing TRTUNII Trial Summary Parameter
Description: 'Primary Treatment Unique Ingredient ID' (TRTUNII) record must be populated in Trial Summary (TS) domain.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for DOSENDTC
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL variable value must be in ISO 8601 format when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD='DOSENDTC'.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for DOSSTDTC
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL variable value must be in ISO 8601 format when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD='DOSSTDTC'.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for EXPSTDTC
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL variable value must be in ISO 8601 format when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD = 'EXPSTDTC'.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for EXPENDTC
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL variable value must be in ISO 8601 format when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD = 'EXPENDTC'.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for DOSDUR
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g., P80Y) or null when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD='DOSDUR'.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for INTSAC
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g., P80Y) or null when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD='INTSAC'.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for TRMSAC
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g., P80Y) or null when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD='TRMSAC'.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for RECSAC
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g., P80Y) or null when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD='RECSAC'.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for AGE
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL must be numeric when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD = 'AGE'.

Message: SETCD value does not present in DM
Description: Set Code (SETCD) values defined in Trial Sets (TX) should be assigned to at least one subject (USUBJID) in Demographics (DM).

Message: Non-unique value for TXSEQ variable within TX domain
Description: Sequence Number (TXSEQ) should be unique within the entire Trial Sets (TX) dataset because there is no Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variable.

Message: Invalid value for --DTHREL
Description: Relationship to Death (--DTHREL) describes the relationship of a particular finding to the death of a subject. Allowed values for this variable include: 'Y' (Caused death), 'N' (Did not cause death), or 'U' (Unknown).

Message: Missing value for --STRESU when --LLOQ is provided
Description: Lower Limit of Quantitation (--LLOQ) should be presented using the same units as those presented in Standard Units (--STRESU). When --LLOQ is provided, --STRESU should also be populated.

Message: SEENDTC is after the latest Disposition date
Description: End Date/Time of Element (SEENDTC) should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC).

Message: EXLOT is populated when EXDOSE equals 0 or is null
Description: If Name of Actual Treatment (EXTRT) is not administered, (i.e., Dose per Administration (EXDOSE) is equal to zero or is not provided), then Lot Number (EXLOT) should be null.

Message: EXLOT is null when EXDOSE is provided
Description: If Name of Actual Treatment (EXTRT) is administered, (i.e., Dose per Administration (EXDOSE) is greater than zero), then Lot Number (EXLOT) should also be provided.

Message: Missing value for --EXCLFL when --REASEX is provided
Description: Exclude from Statistics (--EXCLFL) should be set to 'Y' when Reason for Exclusion from Statistics (--REASEX) is populated.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for ENVTEMPU
Description: --VAL for ENVTEMPU record is the unit for the environmental temperature. Only values of 'C' or 'F' are acceptable.

Message: Duplicate SESTDTC within USUBJID
Description: In the Subject Elements (SE) domain, for each subject, each Element should have a different start date.

Message: Missing value for EXSTDY, when EXENDY is provided
Description: Study Day of Start of Treatment (EXSTDY) variable must be populated, when Study Day of End of Treatment (EXENDY) variable value is provided.

Message: Invalid value for TXVAL for TRTDOS
Description: TXVAL value must be a number, a semicolon-delimited string containing numbers without spaces, or 'SEE PROTOCOL' when TXPARMCD='TRTDOS'

Message: --SEV should not be populated, when --STRESC is 'NORMAL', 'UNREMARKABLE', or null (--STAT = 'NOT DONE')
Description: Severity (--SEV) should not be populated when Result or Finding in Standard Format (--STRESC) is 'NORMAL', 'UNREMARKABLE' or missing (Completion Status (--STAT) = 'NOT DONE').

Message: --DTHREL should not be populated, when --STRESC is 'NORMAL', 'UNREMARKABLE', or null (--STAT = 'NOT DONE')
Description: Relationship to Death (--DTHREL) should not be populated when Result or Finding in Standard Format (--STRESC) is 'NORMAL', 'UNREMARKABLE' or missing (Completion Status (--STAT) = 'NOT DONE').

Message: --CHRON should not be populated, when --STRESC is 'NORMAL', 'UNREMARKABLE', or null (--STAT = 'NOT DONE')
Description: Chronicity of Finding (--CHRON) should not be populated when Result or Finding in Standard Format (--STRESC) is 'NORMAL', 'UNREMARKABLE' or missing (Completion Status (--STAT) = 'NOT DONE').

Message: --DISTR should not be populated, when --STRESC is 'NORMAL', 'UNREMARKABLE', or null (--STAT = 'NOT DONE')
Description: Distribution Pattern of Finding (--DISTR) should not be populated when Result or Finding in Standard Format (--STRESC) is 'NORMAL', 'UNREMARKABLE' or missing (Completion Status (--STAT) = 'NOT DONE').

Message: RFSTDTC does not equal the first treatment date (EXSTDTC)
Description: Reference Start Date (RFSTDTC) variable value must be equal to the first Treatment Start Date (EXSTDTC) unless the animal is a replacement.

Message: QVAL value is not numeric when QNAM = --CALCN
Description: The Numeric Interpretation for Calculations (--CALCN) supplemental qualifier variable should only contain numeric values in QVAL.

Message: Value for FOCID must be more than a number
Description: The value for Focus of Study-Specific Interest (FOCID) must contain more than a number.

Message: Invalid --VAL value for AGETXT
Description: TSVAL/TXVAL value should be populated with 'number-number' format, when TSPARMCD/TXPARMCD='AGETXT'.

Message: Missing TLST record to qualify the test for &quotLast Nonzero Conc&quot for matching time concentration profile
Description: For each record with Parameter Name (PPTEST) containing “to Last Nonzero Conc”,  there must be a record with Parameter Test Code (PPTESTCD) = ”TLST” that contains the same USUBJID, POOLID, PPCAT, PPSPEC and PPNOMDY.

Message: Invalid TSVAL value for SNDIGVER
Description: TSVAL for SNDIGVER record must be a valid term from (SNDIGVER) CT codelist. For SENDIG 3.1.1, this is "SEND IMPLEMENTATION GUIDE VERSION 3.1.1".

Message: Custom domain included for a nonclinical study
Description: A custom domain has been included for a nonclinical study; use should be clearly documented in the nSDRG.

Message: No findings domains included for a nonclinical study
Description: No findings domains have been included for a nonclinical study; the reason should be clearly documented in the nSDRG.

Message: Multiple BASELINE records for the same test
Description: By its definition clinical baseline flags (e.g., last non-missing value prior to first dose) should have only a single record for the same test for subject. Therefore, each subject (USUBJID) should have no more than one record with Baseline Flag (--BLFL) equals 'Y' for the same assessment which is defined by Test (--TESTCD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Method (--METHOD), Specimen (--SPEC), Location (--LOC), Laterality (--LAT) and Directionality (--DIR).
